        <abstract>
            <p>Floral anatomy.</p> 
<p>Wallace’s capital response on reading <hi rend="italic">Origin</hi>.</p>  
<p>E. W. Binney has published on coal-plants living in marine waters ["On the origin of coal", <hi rend="italic">Mem. Lit. &amp; Philos. Soc. Manchester</hi> 2d ser. 8 (1848): 148–94], an old CD idea.</p> 
            <p>Waste of pollen in horse chestnut will make a good case against perfection.</p>
        </abstract>
